rComments: His lectures were engaging and relevant, and the course is an easy A if you follow his lecture notes.
Hes cool

Sasha was one of the most compassionate, engaging, and funny profs Ive ever had. He was very accommodating with a personal issue, and his lectures were always interesting and relevant. Hes very knowledgeable and did his best to answer questions he knew, or would research your question and answer next class. Show up and easy A.
Passionate, engaging teaching style, content fascinating. Tests were challenging but fair and solid study will result in a good grade.

He's a good prof, nice, reasonable, and organizes content clearly. Sometimes a 3 hour lecture can get a little boring but I've had way worse. Also you gotta go to class cause his slides aren't very detailed at all.  dad jokes 10/10 ranting about the environment 11/10

This prof was amazing! By far my favourite prof for first year. He was obviously very passionate about what he was teaching and he always tried to get people to voice their opinions about certain topics. He is very open minded and a very fun person to listen to. The workload for this class is very light, go to class and take good notes. Easy A.

I thought Sasha was hilarious! He's got so many dad jokes. It was great.  Don't skip class because a lot of information about the topics are talked about, but not in the slides. So unless you want to read the textbook then don't skip. His topics are relevant and interesting. It was a night class and I was never fell asleep once.

Prof Kebo is amazing! His lectures are fun and he goes on rants about skeptics and beware population growth!!! The course is not a bird course, you gotta study for it and either choose a volunteering option or a paper to write. The prof is so passionate about the material, so definitely take the course with him!

Great class! Yeah, it can get a tad boring at times, but overall worth taking. Interesting lectures with a prof who clearly cares about not only the material but also the students. Show up to the lectures and pay attention and you'll do well.

He's a pretty solid prof. His lectures make sense all you have to do is write it down. In terms of reading all you really have to do is skim and even then that's not much. He really makes you care about what he's teaching and is open for discussion on it.
Kebo was an awesome prof. He made lectures interesting and actually made me want to go. You can tell he cares about what he's teaching
Very sweet man... he cracks a lot of jokes but his actually lessons are confusing and pointless.

The lectures were long, but the content was easy to work with. He's a funny guy, and is clearly passionate about what he's teaching. The tests were easy to do and as long as you review the notes, you should be fine. Overall, it was a pretty easy and interesting class.

Awesome prof.  His midterm and exam were both very fair, as long as you listen and take notes you should have no problems at all.  He's also very friendly and takes clear interest in what he's teaching

I'm an English literature major so this class was far outside my comfort zone. However the topic was very interesting, and luckily enough for me Prof. Kebo made my decision to take it worthwhile. He was consistently well organized, clear in his lectures and available to answer questions raised by students. Definitely worth getting up for 8:30am.
Amazing teacher, great delivery, very helpful. Made the class very interesting,

Not an easy class.  Very computer heavy, must be at ease with computers.  Professor is very helpful, explains well in class and takes the time to demonstrate things step by step.  Answers emails quuickly.  overall great prof.
Really great course if you study...the prof is really clear and explains well...their is no reason to get a bad mark if you read his slides and the book(pretty straight forward class)

I like the popular culture analogies (star trek, Rush, etc.) He somehow managed to make them very relevant in the course context. Furthermore he was very willing to help if there were concepts I did not understand or simply wanted to discuss in greater depth than the course did. I happen to like human geography, so maybe i am a bit biased
very interesting subject, liked the examples (images useful-helped with clarity).  lots of readings,but still average compared to other classes.

nice guy, awful prof. everyone i knew was failing this class. first midterm 40% average for the class. way too much material to remember, and the questions were pretty unfair. it was his first semester teaching however i think. still pretty difficult class, but interesting. very heavy amounts of readings assigned too
Overall OK.
